12
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,375
<i>♪ And meet friends like this ♪</i>

13
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:31,416
<i>-♪ You just can't miss ♪</i>
-[chorus] Whoa!

14
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,541
<i>-♪ I get curious ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Curious ♪</i>

15
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,791
<i>-♪ And that's marvelous ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Marvelous ♪</i>

16
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:37,916
<i>♪ And that's your reward ♪</i>

17
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,916
<i>♪ You'll never be bored ♪</i>

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,416
<i>♪ If you ask yourself,</i>
<i>"What is this?" ♪</i>

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,416
<i>♪ Like Curious ♪</i>

20
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,375
<i>♪ Like Curious,</i>
<i>Curious George ♪</i>

21
00:00:48,458 --> 00:00:49,458
Oh.

22
00:00:51,041 --> 00:00:54,000
[smooth jazz music]

23
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:59,333
<i>♪♪</i>

24
00:00:59,416 --> 00:01:01,750
[hooting]

25
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,750
[narrator] <i>George was</i>
<i>a going to a new country</i>

26
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,375
<i>where they did things</i>
<i>differently,</i>

27
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:06,916
<i>and he wanted to be prepared.</i>

28
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,041
Oh. [gibbering]

29
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:13,500
George is really excited
about going to Japan,

30
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:14,833
Mr. Okano.

31
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:16,750
He's just about
mastered his chopsticks.

32
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,625
Whoa, whoa, yi!

33
00:01:19,625 --> 00:01:21,583
I can see that.

34
00:01:21,666 --> 00:01:23,458
Hello, George.

35
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:26,458
George, say hi to my old
friend, Mr. Okano.

36
00:01:26,541 --> 00:01:28,083
He's helping me research
the museum's

37
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:30,750
new Snow Festival exhibit.

38
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:33,083
Ah, hi!

39
00:01:33,166 --> 00:01:34,458
Huh?

40
00:01:34,541 --> 00:01:36,625
Ah! [hooting]

41
00:01:36,708 --> 00:01:39,958
Nice to meet you, George.
See you soon!

42
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,666
Bye!

43
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,541
[crash]

44
00:01:45,625 --> 00:01:47,125
Argh!

45
00:01:48,666 --> 00:01:51,125
[narrator] <i>George could hardly</i>
<i>wait to get to Japan.</i>

46
00:01:51,208 --> 00:01:52,750
[gong sounds]

47
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:56,541
[upbeat music]

48
00:01:56,625 --> 00:02:00,000
<i>♪ Take a trip,</i>
<i>see somewhere new ♪</i>

49
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:04,791
<i>♪ Learn about what others</i>
<i>like to do ♪</i>

50
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:07,791
<i>♪♪</i>

51
00:02:07,875 --> 00:02:11,791
<i>♪ There's different words</i>
<i>and different ways ♪</i>

52
00:02:11,875 --> 00:02:16,000
<i>♪ At every turn</i>
<i>you'll be amazed ♪</i>

53
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:18,083
<i>♪♪</i>

54
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:19,791
<i>♪ So head on out ♪</i>

55
00:02:19,875 --> 00:02:21,625
<i>♪♪</i>

56
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:24,375
<i>♪ There's so much to see ♪</i>

57
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:25,916
<i>♪♪</i>

58
00:02:26,041 --> 00:02:28,708
<i>♪ A million things to spark ♪</i>

59
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:32,541
<i>♪ Your curiosity ♪</i>

60
00:02:32,625 --> 00:02:34,083
<i>♪♪</i>

61
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:40,583
<i>♪ There's something there</i>
<i>for every boy and girl ♪</i>

62
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:42,750
<i>♪♪</i>

63
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:47,000
<i>♪ Let's learn about the wonders</i>
<i>of the world ♪</i>

64
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,708
-Ah!
-Wow.

65
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:50,708
Automatic doors!

66
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:54,041
<i>♪ A new way</i>
<i>to say hello ♪</i>

67
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:56,583
<i>♪ Take a seat my friend ♪</i>

68
00:02:56,666 --> 00:02:58,125
<i>♪ Get in the flow ♪</i>

69
00:02:58,208 --> 00:02:59,958
<i>♪ With an open heart ♪</i>

70
00:03:00,041 --> 00:03:01,541
Yay! [laughing]

71
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:03,875
<i>♪ And open mind ♪</i>

72
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:06,666
Ah, ah? Hey.

73
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:10,041
<i>♪ So many sights to see ♪</i>

74
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:13,791
<i>♪ Let's explore</i>
<i>the possibilities ♪</i>

75
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:17,166
<i>♪ It's a show ♪</i>

76
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,083
<i>♪ We're ready to go ♪</i>

77
00:03:19,166 --> 00:03:21,708
<i>♪♪</i>

78
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:26,958
<i>♪ So let's learn about</i>
<i>the wonders of the world ♪</i>

79
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:29,875
<i>♪♪</i>

80
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:31,541
Ahh.

81
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:34,208
Ah! [chattering happily]

82
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:36,875
Aw, I know, George.
It's wonderful.

83
00:03:36,958 --> 00:03:40,458
[dramatic music]

84
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:43,666
Welcome to the Snow Festival.

85
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,583
Ah, hello, Mr. Okano.

86
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:48,541
George, did you know he's the
director of the Snow Festival?

87
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:50,750
<i>Konnichiwa.</i>

88
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:51,875
Huh?

89
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:54,125
That means hello in Japanese.

90
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:57,250
Ah! [gibbering]

91
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,791
Ready for the big tour,
George?

92
00:03:59,875 --> 00:04:01,583
[chattering]

93
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:05,041
How about starting
with some sushi?

94
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:06,666
[gibbering]?

95
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:09,916
Oh, sushi is delicious--
fresh raw fish,

96
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
which is prepared by
specially trained chefs.

97
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:14,875
[hooting]

98
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,083
Ohh!

99
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:24,083
Ah-ah!

100
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,583
[chomping] Ah!

101
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:26,916
[chuckles]
I'm glad you like it.

102
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,083
Ah!

103
00:04:28,166 --> 00:04:30,583
Now, have a look over here.

104
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,250
[narrator] <i>So far, George's trip</i>

105
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:34,125
<i>was everything he'd hoped for.</i>

106
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:36,708
-[squealing]
-Huh?

107
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:38,791
Eh?

108
00:04:38,875 --> 00:04:40,583
[narrator] Another monkey
to play with?

109
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:44,875
[gibbering]

110
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,791
Ooh.

111
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:58,583
[upbeat music]

112
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:05,500
<i>♪♪</i>

113
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:09,750
Wow. Pretty fantastic,
huh, George?

114
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,791
George?

115
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:15,666
Oh, looks like George
found some new friends.

116
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,750
Oh, dear. George!

117
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,625
Be careful!

118
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:22,916
[all hooting]

119
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:26,166
Aw... huh?

120
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,333
Those are wild
Japanese snow monkeys.

121
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:31,833
Wow!

122
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,000
Right here in town?

123
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:34,000
Yes.

124
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,250
They're very smart--

125
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:38,291
and unfortunately,
very mischievous.

126
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,291
[chittering]

127
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,708
[shrieking]

128
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:49,833
Sorry, George, but it's
better to leave them alone

129
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:51,750
if you don't want trouble.

130
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:55,208
Aww. [whimpering]

131
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:56,958
Do not worry.

132
00:05:57,041 --> 00:05:59,625
There's lots more to do
at the festival.

133
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:00,958
Follow me.

134
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:03,083
Ah, okay.

135
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:04,375
Ah!

136
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:07,375
[drumbeat]

137
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:14,291
♪♪

138
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,833
George, you found
the kumi-daiko drummers.

139
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:20,750
A popular sight
at the Festival.

140
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,791
Ooh!

141
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:34,625
[humming]

142
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:38,250
[all chittering]

143
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:48,416
And these sculptures are
the heart of the festival.

144
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,708
Wow!

145
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:52,833
Artists come from
around the world

146
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:53,916
to carve them.

147
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Ooh! [hooting]

148
00:06:57,375 --> 00:07:00,250
[chattering happily]

149
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:04,708
Yes, George, they all start
with a big mound of snow.

150
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:07,041
Oh. [giggling]

151
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:08,833
The snow is good material
for sculpting

152
00:07:08,916 --> 00:07:10,791
because it packs really well.

153
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,000
Oh.

154
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,958
[chattering]

155
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:20,291
Ah!

156
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:25,291
The artists have spent days
carving these masterpieces.

157
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:27,875
Wow!

158
00:07:27,958 --> 00:07:30,458
But all work must finish
by tomorrow;

159
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:33,000
that is when the judges
pick a winner,

160
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:35,375
and it is a great honor.

161
00:07:35,458 --> 00:07:37,958
[chatters excitedly]

162
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:41,000
Whoa, ooh-ooh-ah!

163
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:47,083
Ahh!

164
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:50,125
[man in yellow hat]
Yeah, that is some dragon!

165
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:52,291
Do you think I could
interview the artists?

166
00:07:52,375 --> 00:07:53,791
Of course!

167
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:55,208
You've picked my favorites.

168
00:07:55,291 --> 00:07:57,041
Meet my niece, Yuki...

169
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:58,250
<i>Konnichiwa.</i>

170
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,208
And her husband, Seiji.

171
00:08:00,291 --> 00:08:02,500
<i>Konnichiwa.</i>

172
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:04,250
<i>-Konnichiwa.</i>
-[gibbering]

173
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:07,208
And that is my Uncle Hideki.

174
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:11,500
He has been carving snow
sculptures for decades.

175
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:12,500
[George shouting]

176
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,875
Huh? Chisel!

177
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:16,750
He is a master craftsman--

178
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,083
but also a little clumsy.

179
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,916
[hooting]

180
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:25,500
<i>Domo arigato.</i>

181
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:27,291
Thank you.

182
00:08:27,375 --> 00:08:28,875
Maybe with your help,

183
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:31,833
this will be the year we
finally win the contest.

184
00:08:31,916 --> 00:08:34,166
[chattering]

185
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:37,082
We use special tools
to carve the snow,

186
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:38,916
like this one for the lines.

187
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:42,291
Oh, I see.

188
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:43,957
Would you like to try,
George?

189
00:08:44,041 --> 00:08:44,958
Ooh!

190
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:46,958
[chattering excitedly]

191
00:08:47,041 --> 00:08:48,875
You can practice over there.

192
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:49,958
Aha!

193
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:53,833
Let me show you some
of our other tools.

194
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:57,833
[humming]

195
00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:58,833
Ah!

196
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:00,083
[gasps]

197
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:01,791
Ah?

198
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,083
Ah.

199
00:09:03,166 --> 00:09:04,208
[giggling]

200
00:09:09,958 --> 00:09:11,000
Huh?

201
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:12,333
[narrator] <i>George remembered</i>

202
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:13,791
<i>that the snow monkeys</i>
<i>could be trouble.</i>

203
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,083
<i>But what harm could there be</i>

204
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:17,166
<i>in throwing one</i>
<i>little snowball?</i>

205
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:18,416
Ehhh!

206
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:23,208
[all chittering]

207
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:25,333
Ah! Huh?

208
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:27,875
[narrator] <i>The snow monkeys</i>
<i>played to win.</i>

209
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:30,166
[yelping]

210
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:34,500
Uh, I guess George is ready
for the rest of the tour.

211
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:39,500
I have
arranged for you to see

212
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:42,208
one of our oldest Japanese
traditions,

213
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:44,000
the tea ceremony.

214
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:47,000
Oooh, [gibbering].

215
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,291
You two enjoy.

216
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,041
I must return to the festival.

217
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,333
Bye.

218
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:53,833
Thanks again, Mr. Okano.

219
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:00,916
[whispering]
Now, remember, George,

220
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,416
we have to be quiet.

221
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,583
It's a formal ceremony.

222
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,041
[muttering]

223
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:10,041
[traditional music]

224
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:16,958
<i>♪♪</i>

225
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:18,375
Oooh!

226
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,625
Huh?

227
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:29,333
Mmm.

228
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:32,500
[gulps] Ha!

229
00:10:32,583 --> 00:10:33,541
[gasps]

230
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:35,541
[snow monkey chittering]

231
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,166
[chatters frantically]

232
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:40,333
[both] Shh.

233
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:42,500
Quiet, George.

234
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:44,625
Sorry.

235
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:51,625
[all chittering]

236
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:53,250
[narrator] <i>The snow monkeys?</i>

237
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:57,291
<i>They could upset the whole</i>
<i>tea ceremony!</i>

238
00:10:57,375 --> 00:10:58,416
[gasps]

239
00:10:59,958 --> 00:11:02,500
[whispering] George,
where are you going?

240
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:04,500
[both] Shhhh!

241
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:05,958
[chuckles nervously]

242
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:10,333
[all hooting and hollering]

243
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:13,041
Augh!

244
00:11:13,125 --> 00:11:14,583
Ooh, ooh, ahh!

245
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:16,666
Shh.

246
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:19,583
[narrator] <i>George explained</i>
<i>that the snow monkeys</i>

247
00:11:19,666 --> 00:11:22,000
<i>had to be quiet</i>
<i>and he couldn't play.</i>

248
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:31,625
<i>But, something got lost</i>
<i>in the translation.</i>

249
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:35,250
[monkeys hooting]

250
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:45,208
Oh, no!

251
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:47,666
[screeching]

252
00:11:56,458 --> 00:11:58,458
[chatters frantically]

253
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:07,000
Uh, what do you say we
get out of here

254
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:08,625
before they come back, huh?

255
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:10,750
[murmurs]

256
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:17,708
Ah.

257
00:12:17,791 --> 00:12:19,666
[gibbering]

258
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:22,250
[chuckles]
That's origami, George.

259
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,750
A Japanese art form.

260
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,416
By folding paper,

261
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,583
you can make all sorts
of things.

262
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:28,625
Oh.

263
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:30,250
[gibbering]

264
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:33,000
Sure, let's both do it.

265
00:12:34,125 --> 00:12:36,291
Fold the paper in half.

266
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:38,583
Aha.

267
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,458
Got it?

268
00:12:40,541 --> 00:12:42,458
[squealing]

269
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:46,666
Then fold the top corners
down, like so.

270
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:49,291
[chattering]

271
00:12:49,375 --> 00:12:52,416
-Aw?
-Now fold the bottom piece up,

272
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,750
and you have a hat.

273
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,666
Here you go, monkey.

274
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,666
Ahhh.

275
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,250
Yeah.

276
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:00,625
Huh?

277
00:13:00,708 --> 00:13:01,791
Huh?!

278
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:03,041
Hey!

279
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:04,666
[monkeys chittering]

280
00:13:06,291 --> 00:13:08,250
[hooting]

281
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,333
George, wait!

282
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,291
Remember what Mr. Okano said!

283
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:15,708
[hollering]

284
00:13:15,791 --> 00:13:17,625
Whee!

285
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:22,708
[laughing]

286
00:13:23,875 --> 00:13:25,500
Ha, ha!

287
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:30,125
[chittering]

288
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:33,041
[hooting]

289
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,458
Whoa!

290
00:13:35,541 --> 00:13:36,833
I'm coming, George!

291
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,833
Whoa! Coming through!

292
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:40,500
Pardon me.

293
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:41,833
[grunting]

294
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:45,166
Here I am, George.
Wh-wh-wh-whoa!

295
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,250
[crash]

296
00:13:50,666 --> 00:13:53,291
[monkeys laughing]

297
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:55,583
[sighs]

298
00:13:55,666 --> 00:13:58,083
Maybe it's time to call it
a day, huh, George?

299
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,791
[murmuring]

300
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:10,666
Goodnight, George.

301
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,208
[murmurs]

302
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:16,833
[narrator]
<i>George was disappointed</i>

303
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:18,708
<i>he didn't get to enjoy</i>
<i>the whole tour,</i>

304
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:21,166
<i>all because of those</i>
<i>snow monkeys.</i>

305
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:25,833
Ahhh.

306
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:27,208
[narrator] <i>But maybe there</i>
<i>was a way</i>

307
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:29,166
<i>he could avoid them tomorrow.</i>

308
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:40,416
Come on, George.

309
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:43,666
We don't want to be late
for the snow sculptures.

310
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,208
Huh?

311
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:48,166
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ah.

312
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,166
[giggles]

313
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,541
George!

314
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:53,333
Oh, okay, I really like how
you're embracing

315
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:54,500
Japanese culture.

316
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,375
[murmurs]

317
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:57,791
[narrator] <i>George was certain</i>

318
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,750
<i>that if his friend</i>
<i>didn't recognize him,</i>

319
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:02,583
<i>neither would the snow monkeys.</i>

320
00:15:02,666 --> 00:15:04,666
[indistinct chatter]

321
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:08,875
This is the big day, George.

322
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:10,916
Boy, I really hope Mr. Okano's

323
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,791
family wins today.

324
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,541
[chattering happily]

325
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:18,916
Uh, huh? [gasps]

326
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,666
[monkeys gibbering]

327
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:23,916
Uh-oh.

328
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,666
[humming]

329
00:15:26,916 --> 00:15:30,166
[light dramatic music]

330
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:32,166
[gasps]

331
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:35,166
[grunts]

332
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,583
[straining]

333
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:41,458
[laughter]

334
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,458
Aww!

335
00:15:44,541 --> 00:15:47,666
[all hooting and hollering]

336
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:50,541
[grunts]

337
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:01,750
Whew.

338
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:07,708
Ahhh.

339
00:16:07,791 --> 00:16:09,250
Hi, everybody.

340
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:12,208
Wow, your sculpture
looks amazing!

341
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:13,625
I'm glad you think so.

342
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,333
The judges will be coming soon,

343
00:16:15,416 --> 00:16:16,625
and we're almost finished.

344
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:18,791
Chisel!

345
00:16:18,875 --> 00:16:22,833
Sorry! I mean, I left
the chisel in the tool bag.

346
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:25,416
I need it to carve the eyes.

347
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:26,625
I'll get it.

348
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:34,000
That's funny, I could've sworn
I put the chisel in here.

349
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:35,625
Maybe Seiji has it...

350
00:16:35,708 --> 00:16:37,375
Uh?

351
00:16:37,458 --> 00:16:39,250
Huh.

352
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,500
Aw.

353
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:41,708
[narrator]
<i>George knew those prints</i>

354
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:43,916
<i>in the snow weren't his.</i>

355
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,791
<i>That could only</i>
<i>mean one thing...</i>

356
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:49,375
[chittering]

357
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,458
Hey!

358
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:56,833
[chattering excitedly]

359
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,708
[laughter]

360
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,000
Hey!

361
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:07,790
[all gibbering]

362
00:17:17,083 --> 00:17:19,290
[chittering]

363
00:17:19,375 --> 00:17:21,375
Aha!

364
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,915
Hmm...

365
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,915
[dramatic music]

366
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:29,791
<i>♪♪</i>

367
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:33,375
Aw!

368
00:17:33,458 --> 00:17:35,833
[growling]

369
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:37,875
[hooting]

370
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:40,875
[upbeat jazzy music]

371
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:47,000
<i>♪♪</i>

372
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,041
Uh?

373
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,333
[narrator] <i>How was he</i>
<i>going to get to that rock?</i>

374
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:54,833
[chittering]

375
00:17:54,916 --> 00:17:56,583
[narrator] <i>Maybe he could swim--</i>

376
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:58,958
<i>but the water was</i>
<i>probably freezing.</i>

377
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,083
<i>It wasn't.</i>

378
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:04,333
<i>It was as warm as a bathtub.</i>

379
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,750
[splash]

380
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:09,750
[calm music]

381
00:18:09,833 --> 00:18:15,083
<i>♪♪</i>

382
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:16,083
[gasps]

383
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:17,625
[narrator] <i>The chisel!</i>

384
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:18,916
[all jabbering]

385
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:31,791
Aha! Yeah!

386
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:34,875
[both straining]

387
00:18:38,458 --> 00:18:41,000
Ahhh!

388
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:42,541
Ooh!

389
00:18:47,666 --> 00:18:49,125
Ooh.

390
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:53,583
Yeah! Ha, ha!

391
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:58,541
[muttering]

392
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:03,458
[panting]

393
00:19:03,541 --> 00:19:05,916
[gasps] You found it!

394
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,666
And just in time.

395
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,875
<i>Arigato, </i>George.

396
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:11,458
[chatters]

397
00:19:16,541 --> 00:19:18,791
-Finished!
-Hooray!

398
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:21,875
-Good job, Uncle.
-We did it!

399
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,500
[sighs]

400
00:19:23,583 --> 00:19:25,833
I did not think we
were going to make it.

401
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,833
[gasps]

402
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,583
Ladder!

403
00:19:31,083 --> 00:19:32,416
[overlapping shouts]

404
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:38,750
[man in yellow hat] Oh, boy.
That's not good.

405
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:42,500
-[gong sounds]
-The gong!

406
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:43,916
Here come the judges.

407
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,875
[Yuki] We don't have much time.

408
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:50,041
How will we ever get
enough snow up there

409
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:52,125
to carve a new one?

410
00:19:52,208 --> 00:19:56,541
[whimpering]

411
00:19:56,625 --> 00:19:58,791
I wish we could help, too,
George.

412
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,083
[monkeys jabbering]

413
00:20:04,958 --> 00:20:06,166
[narrator] <i>George realized</i>

414
00:20:06,250 --> 00:20:08,125
<i>there was something</i>
<i>he could do.</i>

415
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:10,916
<i>But he would need help.</i>

416
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,458
Hey! [hooting]

417
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,875
[taunting]

418
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:20,208
[all chittering]

419
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:23,208
[upbeat music]

420
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:25,500
<i>♪♪</i>

421
00:20:25,583 --> 00:20:27,791
Hey! Ah, ah!

422
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:33,208
[laughing]

423
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:36,708
Wait, George. This isn't a
good time for a snowball fight.

424
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:38,750
Aha!

425
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:42,958
It <i>is </i>a good time
for a snowball fight!

426
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:45,041
More to the left, George.

427
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:46,541
[chittering]

428
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:53,458
<i>♪♪</i>

429
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:54,791
[narrator] <i>Luckily for George,</i>

430
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:56,791
<i>this snow stuck together</i>
<i>really well.</i>

431
00:20:56,875 --> 00:20:58,125
Oh.

432
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,750
[chittering]

433
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:04,000
Here you go, George!

434
00:21:05,708 --> 00:21:08,083
[grunting]

435
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:14,833
-We have done it!
-Yeah!

436
00:21:14,916 --> 00:21:16,541
[gasps] Look!

437
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:17,708
The judges!

438
00:21:17,791 --> 00:21:19,625
We're next!

439
00:21:19,708 --> 00:21:21,708
[monkeys grunting]

440
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:32,916
[shouting]

441
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,583
[laughing]

442
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:36,125
Whee!

443
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:38,750
Ha, ha, ha!

444
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:51,041
We award this dragon

445
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:54,166
a prize for best sculpture.

446
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:56,083
-We won!
-We did it!

447
00:21:56,166 --> 00:21:58,083
-[hooting]
-Good job, everybody!

448
00:22:03,083 --> 00:22:05,083
[chattering]

449
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:10,083
[all hooting excitedly]

450
00:22:12,666 --> 00:22:14,833
[narrator] <i>George was happy</i>
<i>for all his new friends.</i>

451
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:17,291
<i>Especially the furry ones.</i>

452
00:22:24,250 --> 00:22:25,750
Hey!

453
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,250
Nice, George.

454
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:30,333
Your origami display is
sure to be a big hit.

455
00:22:30,416 --> 00:22:32,875
Now the exhibit is complete.

456
00:22:32,958 --> 00:22:34,125
Ah!

457
00:22:34,208 --> 00:22:37,083
[fanfare]

458
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:38,208
Aw.

459
00:22:38,291 --> 00:22:40,333
[confused chattering]

460
00:22:40,416 --> 00:22:42,291
[chuckles] Don't worry.

461
00:22:42,375 --> 00:22:44,875
I didn't forget
your favorite part.

462
00:22:44,958 --> 00:22:46,041
Huh?

463
00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:49,208
[gasps] Ah!

464
00:22:49,291 --> 00:22:56,125
<i>♪ So let's learn about</i>
<i>the wonders of the world ♪</i>

465
00:22:57,416 --> 00:23:00,333
[upbeat jazz music]

466
00:23:00,416 --> 00:23:07,250
<i>♪♪</i>

